cs.IT, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the communication between synthetic bacteria nodes using molecular signals, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of a relay node to improve the reliability of communication also involves the study of networked systems (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of different types of molecules for relaying, which falls under the category of molecular modeling (cs.MM) and chemical engineering (cs.CE).
